 Logie (Fife), all named with Old English <i>strǣt</i> ‘paved road, street’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Stratton  ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":86,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":95,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When de Stratton was born about 1129, in England, her father, Mathew Stratton, was 31 and her mother, Mrs Mathew Stratton, was 26. She married Henry de Stawell in 1149, in Cothelstone, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1129–":"umbes 1129–Surnud","1129–Female":"1129–Surnud","1129–Male":"1129–Surnud","1159–Male":"1159–Surnud","1099–Male":"1099–Surnud","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","1129":"1129","1149":"1149","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1104":"1104","about 1129":"umbes 1129","1224":"1224","1124":"1124","1099":"1099","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1129–":"noin 1129–Kuollut","1129–Female":"1129–Kuollut","1129–Male":"1129–Kuollut","1159–Male":"1159–Kuollut","1099–Male":"1099–Kuollut","1104–Female":"1104–Kuollut","1129":"1129","1149":"1149","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1104":"1104","about 1129":"noin 1129","1224":"1224","1124":"1124","1099":"1099","Cothelstone, Somerset, England":"Cothelstone, Somerset, England